<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-86-0086 </DOCNO><TEXT>The 15 papers contributed to the international meeting by working group1 'Energy conservation and operation of vessels' were dealing with thefollowing subjects: international energy marketing and pricing trends;automation as a vehicle used by the shipping industry and crews to reducethe fuel consumption of trading vessels; fuel saving education in theframe of the training for foreign going captains; economic efficiencyof modern navigation strategies; a selection of experiences and resultsgained in merchant marine energy conservation; the effects of hydrometeorologicalfactors on shipping, the effects of hydrometeorological factors on weatherwatching; speed control on trading vessels approaching seaports; resultsand problems of the prediction of design data vessel controllability;planning and projecting of energy-saving types of ships of differenttonnages. (HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>